# Claude (opus) — 2026-03-17 13:26:03
# Duration: 746s — Exit: 0
# Prompt:
#   /spec:create Improve title extraction algorithm based on feedback from iteration 30
#   
#   Context for spec creation:
#   - Read the feedback at tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/feedback.md
#   - Read the current implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts
#   - Read previous iteration docs in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand what has been tried
#   
#   Hard constraints:
#   - Must run on a mobile device (React Native / Expo)
#   - Total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds
#   - Changes land in lib/text-classifier/ and related files
#   
#   Everything else is open for debate. The current approach (MiniLM embeddings + heuristic scoring)
#   is one option, but you are free to propose alternatives if they'd work better:
#   - Different embedding model or similarity strategy
#   - Replacing embeddings entirely with a rule-based or hybrid approach
#   - Restructuring the pipeline (e.g., two-pass, re-ranking, candidate merging)
#   - Changing how candidates are generated, filtered, or deduplicated
#   - Any other approach that solves the failures within the hard constraints
#   
#   Don't be incremental for the sake of it — if the feedback reveals a fundamental design flaw,
#   propose a fundamental fix. But also don't change things that already work well.
#   
#   IMPORTANT: Write the spec to tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/improvement-plan.md (not to specs/ directory).
#   Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the improvement-plan.md file.

============================================================

The improvement plan is written to `tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/improvement-plan.md`.

**Key finding:** The iter 29 plan correctly identified OCR repair and cooking instruction issues but missed the real blocker — the continuation-line merge in `buildCandidates` (lines 646–658) treats `(` as a continuation character, which merges the `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` annotation lines into the title. The merged result fails the ≥8-word hard filter, and the original standalone title is never generated as a candidate. This single bug accounts for 6 of the 9 failures.

**The 4 proposed changes:**

1. **Preserve standalone when merging** — always emit the original line before also emitting the merged form. Fixes 6/9 failures.
2. **Add "sole" to food dictionary** — enables dictionary-guided repair of `S01e → Sole`. Fixes 1 failure.
3. **Lower Polish cooking instruction word threshold to 2** — catches `Ugotuj ziemniaky.` as an instruction. Fixes 1 failure.
4. **Raise positional cap for pipe+ALL_CAPS** — helps `OGÓRKOWA ZUPA` clear the embedding threshold. Fixes 1 failure.

Expected outcome: 8/9 failures fixed, ~99.1% accuracy. The remaining failure (Mushroom Risotto) is unfixable — the title doesn't appear in the document.
