{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0125aX2tjv5z76brxZvnaJty","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Iteration 29 → 30 Improvement Plan\n     2→\n     3→**Status:** Draft\n     4→**Date:** 2026-03-17\n     5→**Baseline:** 91.9% combined accuracy (9 failures, all generated; 0 real failures)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Overview\n    10→\n    11→Nine generated-file failures remain, clustered into three root causes:\n    12→\n    13→1. **Incomplete mixed-case OCR repair** — the blind repair path (`applyBlindOcrRepairToken`) only substitutes `1→i/l`, `¡→i`, `€→e` in mixed-case context. It misses `0→o`, `4→a`, `5→s`, which the ALL_CAPS branch handles. This causes Pattern 7 (partial repair) and contributes to Patterns 1–4 where partially-repaired titles fail hard filters or score poorly.\n    14→\n    15→2. **Missing Polish cooking verb prefixes** — `looksLikeCookingInstruction` and `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` don't cover perfective forms like `ugotuj` (u+gotuj), `upiecz` (u+piecz), `podawać/podaw4ć` (serve). Body lines starting with these verbs pass hard filters and can outscore the actual title.\n    16→\n    17→3. **Garbled tokens evade multi-word detection** — `isLikelyGarbled` catches single-word `[a-z][A-Z]` transitions (line 302) but not multi-word candidates containing such tokens. `XxYyZz salt and pepper` passes because the garbled check only fires for `words.length === 1`.\n    18→\n    19→Pattern 6 (Mushroom Risotto — title absent from document) is a structural/scan problem where the actual recipe title doesn't appear in the text. The extractor correctly identifies the best title-like line; it's just the wrong recipe. This is **not fixable** without external context and is excluded from this plan.\n    20→\n    21→---\n    22→\n    23→## Goals\n    24→\n    25→- Fix Patterns 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7 (8 of 9 failures)\n    26→- Maintain 100% accuracy on real files\n    27→- No regressions on currently-passing generated files\n    28→- Keep total extraction time under 10 seconds on device\n    29→\n    30→## Non-Goals\n    31→\n    32→- Fix Pattern 6 (title absent from document) — requires page-level context\n    33→- Change the embedding model or similarity strategy — MiniLM works well for the 102+ passing cases\n    34→- Restructure the candidate generation pipeline — it's architecturally sound\n    35→\n    36→---\n    37→\n    38→## Detailed Changes\n    39→\n    40→### Change A: Complete mixed-case blind OCR repair\n    41→\n    42→**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, function `applyBlindOcrRepairToken` (lines 845–857)\n    43→\n    44→**Problem:** The mixed-case branch only handles three substitutions:\n    45→```typescript\n    46→// Current mixed-case path (lines 852-856):\n    47→.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])1/g, oneLetter)\n    48→.replace(/1(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, oneLetter)\n    49→.replace(/¡/g, \"i\")\n    50→.replace(/€/g, \"e\")\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→Missing: `0→o`, `4→a`, `5→s` — all present in the ALL_CAPS branch (lines 879–884) but absent from mixed-case. This directly causes Pattern 7 (`S01e` → `S0ie` instead of `Sole`) and weakens repair of Patterns 1–4.\n    54→\n    55→**Fix:** Add the missing substitutions with lowercase-adjacent context guards:\n    56→```typescript\n    57→// After the existing 1→oneLetter and ¡→i replacements, add:\n    58→.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])0/g, \"o\")\n    59→.replace(/0(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"o\")\n    60→.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])4/g, \"a\")\n    61→.replace(/4(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"a\")\n    62→.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])5/g, \"s\")\n    63→.replace(/5(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"s\")\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→The lookaround guards (requiring adjacent lowercase letters) prevent false positives on legitimate digits in titles like \"Variation 4\" or \"Page 50\".\n    67→\n    68→**Also update `generateBlindOcrVariants`** (lines 920–938): the dual-variant logic currently only varies `1→i` vs `1→l`. With `0→o` added, `S01e` will now produce `Sole` in a single pass (both `0→o` and `1→i` fire). No dual-variant needed for `0`.\n    69→\n    70→**Impact:** Fixes Pattern 7 directly. Strengthens repair for Patterns 1–4 by ensuring the blind repair path produces cleaner candidates that score better in embeddings.\n    71→\n    72→**Risk:** Low. The lookaround guards prevent over-application. The ALL_CAPS branch already applies these substitutions unconditionally.\n    73→\n    74→---\n    75→\n    76→### Change B: Expand garbled token detection to multi-word candidates\n    77→\n    78→**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, function `isLikelyGarbled` (lines 271–337)\n    79→\n    80→**Problem:** The `[a-z][A-Z]` internal transition check (line 302) only fires for single-word candidates (`words.length === 1`). Multi-word candidates like `XxYyZz salt and pepper` pass because `XxYyZz` is never checked individually for the transition pattern."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a56c14a-0bc6-452a-98e5-f30796680f9b","uuid":"8b6664f2-1d2a-4ae8-9c92-0c71d735b1bf","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/29-e7e3098/improvement-plan.md","content":"# Iteration 29 → 30 Improvement Plan\n\n**Status:** Draft\n**Date:** 2026-03-17\n**Baseline:** 91.9% combined accuracy (9 failures, all generated; 0 real failures)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nNine generated-file failures remain, clustered into three root causes:\n\n1. **Incomplete mixed-case OCR repair** — the blind repair path (`applyBlindOcrRepairToken`) only substitutes `1→i/l`, `¡→i`, `€→e` in mixed-case context. It misses `0→o`, `4→a`, `5→s`, which the ALL_CAPS branch handles. This causes Pattern 7 (partial repair) and contributes to Patterns 1–4 where partially-repaired titles fail hard filters or score poorly.\n\n2. **Missing Polish cooking verb prefixes** — `looksLikeCookingInstruction` and `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` don't cover perfective forms like `ugotuj` (u+gotuj), `upiecz` (u+piecz), `podawać/podaw4ć` (serve). Body lines starting with these verbs pass hard filters and can outscore the actual title.\n\n3. **Garbled tokens evade multi-word detection** — `isLikelyGarbled` catches single-word `[a-z][A-Z]` transitions (line 302) but not multi-word candidates containing such tokens. `XxYyZz salt and pepper` passes because the garbled check only fires for `words.length === 1`.\n\nPattern 6 (Mushroom Risotto — title absent from document) is a structural/scan problem where the actual recipe title doesn't appear in the text. The extractor correctly identifies the best title-like line; it's just the wrong recipe. This is **not fixable** without external context and is excluded from this plan.\n\n---\n\n## Goals\n\n- Fix Patterns 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7 (8 of 9 failures)\n- Maintain 100% accuracy on real files\n- No regressions on currently-passing generated files\n- Keep total extraction time under 10 seconds on device\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Fix Pattern 6 (title absent from document) — requires page-level context\n- Change the embedding model or similarity strategy — MiniLM works well for the 102+ passing cases\n- Restructure the candidate generation pipeline — it's architecturally sound\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Changes\n\n### Change A: Complete mixed-case blind OCR repair\n\n**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, function `applyBlindOcrRepairToken` (lines 845–857)\n\n**Problem:** The mixed-case branch only handles three substitutions:\n```typescript\n// Current mixed-case path (lines 852-856):\n.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])1/g, oneLetter)\n.replace(/1(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, oneLetter)\n.replace(/¡/g, \"i\")\n.replace(/€/g, \"e\")\n```\n\nMissing: `0→o`, `4→a`, `5→s` — all present in the ALL_CAPS branch (lines 879–884) but absent from mixed-case. This directly causes Pattern 7 (`S01e` → `S0ie` instead of `Sole`) and weakens repair of Patterns 1–4.\n\n**Fix:** Add the missing substitutions with lowercase-adjacent context guards:\n```typescript\n// After the existing 1→oneLetter and ¡→i replacements, add:\n.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])0/g, \"o\")\n.replace(/0(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"o\")\n.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])4/g, \"a\")\n.replace(/4(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"a\")\n.replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])5/g, \"s\")\n.replace(/5(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"s\")\n```\n\nThe lookaround guards (requiring adjacent lowercase letters) prevent false positives on legitimate digits in titles like \"Variation 4\" or \"Page 50\".\n\n**Also update `generateBlindOcrVariants`** (lines 920–938): the dual-variant logic currently only varies `1→i` vs `1→l`. With `0→o` added, `S01e` will now produce `Sole` in a single pass (both `0→o` and `1→i` fire). No dual-variant needed for `0`.\n\n**Impact:** Fixes Pattern 7 directly. Strengthens repair for Patterns 1–4 by ensuring the blind repair path produces cleaner candidates that score better in embeddings.\n\n**Risk:** Low. The lookaround guards prevent over-application. The ALL_CAPS branch already applies these substitutions unconditionally.\n\n---\n\n### Change B: Expand garbled token detection to multi-word candidates\n\n**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, function `isLikelyGarbled` (lines 271–337)\n\n**Problem:** The `[a-z][A-Z]` internal transition check (line 302) only fires for single-word candidates (`words.length === 1`). Multi-word candidates like `XxYyZz salt and pepper` pass because `XxYyZz` is never checked individually for the transition pattern.","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":302}}}
