{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RsQkwFRP1P8KbUuHviCHqV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So `with` is in the dictionary. `w1th` should dictionary-repair to `with`. `Bra1sed` should repair to `braised`. `W1ne` should repair to `wine`. `D1p` should repair to `dip`. But the title extractor is still returning empty for these cases. Let me understand why — the issue might be that the repaired candidate still fails a hard filter.\n\nLet me trace through `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne`:\n1. `repairOcrText` runs on each word: `Bra1sed` → checks dictionary → `braised` is in dict → `Braised`. `w1th` → `with`. `Wh1te` → `white`? Let me check: `wh1te` with `1→i` = `white` and `1→l` = `whlte`. `white` is in dict, so it repairs. `W1ne` → `wine` is in dict.\n2. After repair: `Braised Cod with White Wine` — this should pass hard filters.\n\nBut wait — this repair happens in `buildCandidates` (line 681: `repairOcrText(stripParentheticalGloss(stripTrailingPageRef(stripPageNumber(line.text))))`). So the repaired text should be a candidate. But the result is empty. Something is blocking it earlier.\n\nLet me check — could the `isLikelyGarbled` check be catching the raw text before repair?\n\nActually, looking more carefully at `buildCandidates`: line 681 applies `repairOcrText` to produce `singleText`, then checks `passesHardFilters(singleText)`. But `passesHardFilters` calls `isLikelyGarbled` which checks for vowel ratios and other things. Let me trace `Braised Cod with White Wine` through `passesHardFilters` — this should pass all filters fine.\n\nWait — the issue might be more subtle. Let me check if `repairOcrText(\"Bra1sed\")` actually returns `Braised`. The function does per-word repair via `repairOcrWord`. For `Bra1sed`: lowercase = `bra1sed`, positions = [{index: 3, replacements: [\"i\", \"l\"]}]. Generates `braised` and `bralSed`. `braised` is in FOOD_DICTIONARY → returns `Braised`. Good.\n\nFor `w1th`: lowercase = `w1th`, positions = [{index: 1, replacements: [\"i\", \"l\"]}]. Generates `with` and `wlth`. `with` is in dictionary → returns `with`. Good.\n\nSo after dictionary repair: `Braised Cod with White Wine`. This should work.\n\nUnless... the `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` line on line 3 is interfering. Let me look at `findBurstEnd` logic more carefully.\n\nActually, wait. Line 3 of the input is `(OCR CORRUPTION: digit for letter, hyphenation)`. This is caught by `passesHardFilters` at line 437: `if (/^\\(OCR\\b/i.test(text.trim())) return false;`. So it's filtered. Good.\n\nBut then `lngredients:` on line 5 — `isSectionLabel` catches this via OCR normalization (`l→i` = `ingredients`). So it's also filtered.\n\nThe first candidate should be `Braised Cod with White Wine` (after dictionary repair of line 1). Unless `findBurstEnd` is skipping line 1!\n\nLet me trace `findBurstEnd`:\n- Line 0: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne` — length is 30 (> 20), so the while loop at line 500 doesn't skip it. \n- Actually wait — `findBurstEnd` checks `lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text) && !isAllCaps(lines[i].text)`. Line 0's text is 30 chars, so it's not < 20 → loop exits. `burstEnd = 0`. Good.\n\nBut then the body-content prologue check at line 507: `if (i === 0)` — it checks if consecutive lines are cooking instructions, prose, or body-ending. Line 0 `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne` is not a cooking instruction, not lowercase-start continuation, not body-ending. So `j` stays at 0, and `j < 3` → no skip. Good.\n\nSo line 0 should become a candidate. After dictionary repair it should be `Braised Cod with White Wine`. This passes all hard filters. It should score well against the title reference embedding.\n\nBut the result is empty. Something is wrong. Let me check if there's a log with scoring details...\n\nActually, let me look at this differently. The feedback says \"got empty string\". Maybe the issue is in the threshold or post-processing. Let me look at the remaining code."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":85519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a56c14a-0bc6-452a-98e5-f30796680f9b","uuid":"07c1e0ee-c34f-44b7-8542-6425af30f576"}
