inal line 0 with the merged form, and `i++` skips the next line.\n\nLet me verify by checking lines 646-658:\n\n```typescript\nfor (let i = 0; i < capsCoalesced.length; i++) {\n    const line = capsCoalesced[i];\n    if (i + 1 < capsCoalesced.length) {\n      const nextText = capsCoalesced[i + 1].text;\n      if (/^[/&+:(]/.test(nextText)) {\n        mergedLines.push({ text: `${line.text} ${nextText}`, index: line.index });\n        i++;\n        continue;\n      }\n    }\n    mergedLines.push(line);\n  }\n```\n\nYes — when line 0 is merged with line 1 (which starts with `(`), only the merged form enters `mergedLines`. The original line 0 is lost.\n\nThen in the candidate generation loop (line 674+), the single text is `repairOcrText(stripParentheticalGloss(stripTrailingPageRef(stripPageNumber(mergedText))))`. The merged text is very long and fails hard filters. The original short form never gets a chance.\n\n**This is the fundamental root cause for Patterns A and B.** The `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` parenthetical annotation lines start with `(` which triggers the continuation merge, destroying the title candidate.\n\nNow let me check if this also affects the other failures.\n\nFor `Drożdże Sern1k`:\n- Line 0: `Drożdże Sern1k`\n- Line 2: `(OCR CORRUPTION: digit for letter, dotless i, garbage tokens)`\n- The continuation merge triggers because `(` starts line 2 → merged into `Drożdże Sern1k (OCR CORRUPTION: digit for letter, dotless i, garbage tokens)` → too many words → rejected.\n\nFor `Kopytka z Pieczarkami Leśnymi`:\n- Line 0: `KoPyTka z P¡eczarkami Leśnymi`\n- Line 2: `Kopytka, zwane też kopy-tkami, to małe` — starts with `K`, not `(`. So no merge. This one must have a different issue.\n\nFor `Żurek Krakowski`:\n- Line 0: `Żurek Krakowski`\n- Line 2: `(OCR CORRUPTION: dotless i, garbage tokens, hyphenation)` — starts with `(` → merge!\n\nFor `Piernik z Śliwkami`:\n- Line 0: `P1ern1k z Śliwkami`\n- Line 2: `(OCR CORRUPTION: digit for letter)` — starts with `(` → merge!\n\nFor `Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip`:\n- Line 0: `Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p`\n- Line 2: `(OCR CORRUPTION: digit/letter mix, garbage, hyphenation)` — starts with `(` → merge!\n\nFor `Sole with Brown Butter and Capers`:\n- Line 0: `S01e with Brown Butter and Capers`\n- Line 2: ?? Let me check."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":118194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a56c14a-0bc6-452a-98e5-f30796680f9b","uuid":"35fcfd3d-8c73-47c0-85b9-33d5103d2df0"}
