{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012FvUZS3UywESf3UZzSEBum","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The improvement plan is written to `tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/improvement-plan.md`.\n\n**Key finding:** The iter 29 plan correctly identified OCR repair and cooking instruction issues but missed the real blocker — the continuation-line merge in `buildCandidates` (lines 646–658) treats `(` as a continuation character, which merges the `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` annotation lines into the title. The merged result fails the ≥8-word hard filter, and the original standalone title is never generated as a candidate. This single bug accounts for 6 of the 9 failures.\n\n**The 4 proposed changes:**\n\n1. **Preserve standalone when merging** — always emit the original line before also emitting the merged form. Fixes 6/9 failures.\n2. **Add \"sole\" to food dictionary** — enables dictionary-guided repair of `S01e → Sole`. Fixes 1 failure.\n3. **Lower Polish cooking instruction word threshold to 2** — catches `Ugotuj ziemniaky.` as an instruction. Fixes 1 failure.\n4. **Raise positional cap for pipe+ALL_CAPS** — helps `OGÓRKOWA ZUPA` clear the embedding threshold. Fixes 1 failure.\n\nExpected outcome: 8/9 failures fixed, ~99.1% accuracy. The remaining failure (Mushroom Risotto) is unfixable — the title doesn't appear in the document."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5353,"cache_read_input_tokens":120205,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5353},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a56c14a-0bc6-452a-98e5-f30796680f9b","uuid":"812deda9-49d5-4c87-9917-03857d583365"}
